api.api.mock.script.readme:
Use scripts personalizados para obter parâmetros de solicitação do usuário e modificar a mensagem de resposta.
**Example Code**
~~~javascript
// Get mock data from Smart Mock
var responseJson = {appScriptMainObject}.mockResponse.json();
// Modify the paged data from responseJson
// Set page as the page in request parameter
responseJson.page = {appScriptMainObject}.mockRequest.getParam("page");
// Set total as 120
responseJson.total = 120;
// Write the modified json into {appScriptMainObject}.mockResponse
{appScriptMainObject}.mockResponse.setBody(responseJson);
~~~
**Request: {appScriptMainObject}.mockRequest**
:::tip
\$$.mockRequest object is the same as Postman's pm.request object ([Reference](https://www.postmanlabs.com/postman-collection/Request.html)).
The differences between \$$.mockRequest and pm.request are:
1. Added $$.mockRequest.getParam(key: string) method
2. Added $$.mockRequest.cookies
:::
~~~javascript
// Get parameters of request
var userId = $$.mockRequest.getParam("userId");
// Get headers of request
var userId = $$.mockRequest.headers.get("userId");
// Get cookies of request
var userId = $$.mockRequest.cookies.get("userId");
// Get the json data in the request body
var requestJsonData = $$.mockRequest.body.toJSON();
// Get the string data in the request body
var requestStringData = $$.mockRequest.body.toString();
// Get the form-data data in the request body
var userId = $$.mockRequest.body.formdata.get("userId");
// Get the urlencoded data in the request body
var userId = $$.mockRequest.body.urlencoded.get("userId");
~~~
**Response: {appScriptMainObject}.mockResponse**
:::tip
\$$.mockResponse object is the same as Postman's pm.response object ([Reference](https://www.postmanlabs.com/postman-collection/Response.html)).
The differences between \$$.mockResponse and pm.response are:
1. Added \$$.mockResponse.setBody(body: any) method.
2. Added \$$.mockResponse.setCode(code: number) method.
3. Added \$$.mockResponse.setDelay(duration: number) method.
:::
~~~javascript
// Get the response auto-generated
var responseJsonData = $$.mockResponse.json();
// Set body for response with JSON
$$.mockResponse.setBody({setBody});
// Set body for response with string
$$.mockResponse.setBody("Hello World!");
// Set the HTTP status code returned
$$.mockResponse.setCode(200);
// Set the Mock response delay in milliseconds
$$.mockResponse.setDelay(3000);
// Get HTTP status code
var statusCode = $$.mockResponse.code;
// Get HTTP header
var myHeader = $$.mockResponse.headers.get("X-My-Header");
// Delete a header with a key, X-My-Header, in the current request.
$$.mockResponse.headers.remove("X-My-Header")
// Add a header with a key, X-My-Header, in the current request.
$$.mockResponse.headers.add({addHeader});
// Upsert a header with a key, X-My-Header, in the current request. If the key already exists, it will be modified.
$$.mockResponse.headers.upsert({addHeader})
~~~
**Mock Priority Description**
Priority of rule matching while requesting Mock data: Expectations in Advanced Mock > Custom Mock Scripts.
If the expectation in the Advanced Mock was matched, the custom Mock script would not be called.

